The paper discusses the limitations of relational database management systems and proposes a new approach for exploiting fuzzy relational databases. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the database (cs.DB) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses flexible querying and repairing and substituting unanswered queries, which are topics related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper proposes a new technique for extracting summary fuzzy data, which could fall under the sub-category of signal processing (cs.SI).
